# React TypeScript Rules

Use:

- TypeScript strict mode
- functional components
- hooks
- composition

Avoid:

- class components
- unnecessary state
- unnecessary effects
- prop drilling when avoidable

Components:

- Keep components focused.
- Extract reusable logic into hooks.
- Keep business logic outside UI components.
- Preffer PrimeReact over custom implementation when possible
- Avoid raw css use in line style if it is up to 2 properties otherwise use styled-components
- when needed to show a lot of data prioritize virtualization and pagination

State:

Consider:

- loading state
- error state
- empty state
- stale data
- race conditions
- incorrect or out of schema data

Async:

Always consider:

- cancellation
- retries
- duplicate requests
- cleanup

Performance:

Avoid premature optimization.

Use memoization only when it provides value.

Accessibility:

Always consider:

- keyboard navigation
- semantic HTML
- ARIA when needed
